msgid "Unit and Integration Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1151
msgid "Elgg's PHPUnit bootstrap can now handle both unit and integration tests. Please note that **you shouldn't run tests on a production site**, as it may damage data integrity. To prevent data loss, you need to specify database settings via environment variables. You can do so via the phpunit.xml bootstrap."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1155
msgid "Plugins can now implement their own PHPUnit tests by extending ``\\Elgg\\UnitTestCase`` and ``\\Elgg\\IntegrationTestCase`` classes. ``plugins`` test suite will automatically autoload PHPUnit tests from ``mod/<plugin_id>/tests/phpunit/unit`` and ``mod/<plugin_id>/tests/phpunit/integration``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1159
msgid "Prior to running integration tests, you need to enable the plugins that you wish to test alongside core API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1161
msgid "``\\Elgg\\IntegrationTestCase`` uses ``\\Elgg\\Seeding`` trait, which can be used to conveniently build new entities and write them to the database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1164
msgid "``\\Elgg\\UnitTestCase`` does not use the database, but provides a database mocking interface, which allows tests to define query specs with predefined returns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1167
msgid "By default, both unit and integration tests will be run whenever ``phpunit`` is called. You can use ``--testsuite`` flag to only run a specific suite: ``phpunit --testsuite unit`` or ``phpunit --testsuite integration`` or ``phpunit --testsuite plugins``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1169
msgid "For integration testing to run properly, plugins are advised to not put any logic into the root of ``start.php``, and instead return a Closure. This allows the testsuite to build a new Application instance without loosing plugin initialization logic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1172
msgid "Plugins with simpletests will continue working as perviously. However, method signatures in the ``ElggCoreUnitTest`` abstract class have changed and you will need to update your tests accordingly. Namely, it's discouraged to use ``__construct`` and ``__desctruct`` methods. ``setUp`` and ``tearDown`` have been marked as private and are used for consistent test boostrapping and asserting pre and post conditions, your test case should use ``up`` and ``down`` methods instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix/upgrade-notes/2.x-to-3.0.rst:1177
msgid "Simpletests can no longer be executed from the admin interface of the developers plugin. Use Elgg cli command: ``elgg-cli simpletest``"
msgstr ""

